Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses results related to specific graph classes such as chordal graphs, doubly chordal graphs, split graphs, cographs, and chain graphs, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper proposes algorithms for solving the problem in specific graph classes, which could also classify it under cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses upper bounds and randomized algorithms, which could classify it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
